      <description>&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Sancianco y Goson, Gregorio: El progreso de Filipinas. Estudios económicos, administrativos y políticos. Parte económica. Madrid, Imp. de la Vda. de J M. Perez, 1881 Pp XIV-260.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;An eminent student of Philippine life and history, James A. LeRoy in his &amp;ldquo;The Philippines, 1860-1898—Some comment and bibliographical notes&amp;rdquo; published in volume 52 of Blair and Robertson, Philippine Islands 1493-1898, praises this book (p. 141) as &amp;ldquo;especially valuable on administrative matters just prior to the revision of the fiscal regime in connection with the abolition of the government tobacco monopoly&amp;rdquo;, and for its &amp;ldquo;data on land, commerce, and industry&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
